<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Phone Backup Portal</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="container">
      <h1>Backup photos from your phone to your computer</h1>
      <p class="muted">
        Upload from your phone, then download everything to your computer in one
        zip. Files stay on the server until you or an admin delete them, but
        storage is limited per user.
      </p>
      <div class="card actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="/signup">Get started – create account</a>
        <a class="button" href="/login">Already have an account? Log in</a>
      </div>
      <section class="card" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <h2>How to use this tool</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Sign up on your computer</strong> – create an account and
            sign in.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Go to Settings</strong> – set up your folders and get your
            personal upload link or QR code.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Open the link on your phone</strong> – log in with the same
            account and pick a folder.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Upload photos and videos</strong> – choose the files you
            want to send to the server.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Download on your computer</strong> – open “Folders” or
            “Uploads” and click “Download all” to save everything locally.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Clear old data when done</strong> – delete folders, files,
            or even your account to free up server space.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

